window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p><b><i>Travis Holt thought he could outrun his past.</i></b></p> <p>Abby Westwood barely escaped an attack at her apartment, and now she’s on the run. Her only refuge? Misty Mountain, a remote and wild place tied to secrets of her brother’s death. Desperate for answers, she seeks out one man who might hold them, Travis Holt.</p> <p>Once a Navy SEAL, now a recluse hidden deep in the Rockies, Travis has spent years burying his demons beneath the snow-covered silence of Misty Mountain. But when Abby arrives, his world fractures. She’s the sister of the man he swore to protect. And she’s being hunted.</p> <p>Abby never believed the official story behind her brother’s death. Her search for truth leads her straight into the arms of the one man her brother told her to find. But Travis is nothing like she expected, colder than the mountain air, harder than the steel resolve in his storm-gray eyes. And yet, when danger comes knocking, he becomes her shield, her protector…her only chance at survival.</p> <p>Snowed in together, the heat between them burns hotter than the fire in his cabin. As deadly enemies close in, Travis must decide, stay in the shadows and let Abby go, or fight back and claim what’s his.</p> <p>Because the past isn’t done with them. And this time, Travis Holt isn’t running.</p> <p>For fans of rugged mountain men, pulse-pounding suspense, and sizzling romance, <b>Shadow of Misty Mountain</b> is a gripping tale of danger, desire, and unbreakable bonds.</p> <p>The small Colorado town of Misty Mountain appears to be a peaceful, perfect haven. Beneath the surface, however, it’s brimming with secrets, love, and undeniable chemistry. Get ready for steamy encounters at the rustic Hollow Tree Inn, forbidden rendezvous under Whispering Falls, strangers with dark histories, and locals with unspoken desires. In Misty Mountain, love isn’t just complicated—it’s downright explosive.</p>"; 
